2^{10 - x} \cdot 2^{10 - x} = 4^{10-x}
 2^{10 - x} \cdot 2^{10 - x}\;\; = \;\; (2)^{10 - x + 10 - x} \; = \; (2)^{2 \cdot (10 - x)} \;=\; 4^{10 - x}\tag{1} 
 \frac{4^x}{2^y} =  2^{x - y} \tag{2} 
\text{Yes:}\;\;\;\large 2^{10 - x} \cdot 2^{10 - x} =\; 4^{10-x}\tag{1.a}
\underbrace{\large 2^{10 - x} \cdot 2^{10 - x}  = (2)^{10 - x + 10 - x} = (2)^{2 \cdot (10 - x)} = 4^{10 - x}}\tag{1.b} 
\text{Yes, that is that is allowed.}
\underbrace{ \large \frac{4^x}{2^y} =  2^{x - y}}\;\;\; ?\tag{2 ?}
\text{NOT correct. See below:}
(2)\quad \large \frac{4^x}{2^y} \;=\; 4^x \cdot 2^{-y} \;= \;(2^2)^x \cdot 2^{-y} \;=\; 2^{(2x)} \cdot 2^{(-y)} \;=\;2^{(2x-y)}
4^x/2^y = 2^{2x-y}
